summary: Here's What Jon Snow Might Do About Daenerys On "Game Of Thrones"
body:
Here’s What Jon Snow Might Do About Daenerys On “Game Of Thrones”

Aside from mentioning the AA prophesy, one can get good sense from BuzzFeed sometimes.

One reason I feel that people set on that literal reading of the AA prophecy are barking up the wrong tree is that no one on the show has mentioned it on AGES, even with all the talk of defeating the AotD. They beat us over the head with “ooh, but Dany can’t have babies” last season, for a reason, but we haven’t heard about AA and Nissa Nissa in AGES.

summary: I watched the first episode of season 8 of Game of Thrones last night and it was really awesome!  It seems Sansa really hates...
caption:
I watched the first episode of season 8 of Game of Thrones last night and it was really awesome!

 It seems Sansa really hates Daenerys, I guess I get that since her brother Jon was King of the North and probably shouldn’t have given up his title so easily. But as he pointed out it was so he could gain access and use her army and dragons so he forfeit his title to her. It did mean some others didn’t let their men fight with them though … so that wasn’t so good.

Sansa also came up with the obvious, how would they feed all these new warriors? they hadn’t planned for all of them too. Good question and about what the dragons eat. I jokingly said people, which yeah they do but she said whatever they like which is also true and could mean they could eat a ton of people which they don’t want. 

Jon and Dany went on a dragon ride to some remote location to make love, but Jon got the evil eye from one of the dragons who was like “excuse me son, what do you think you’re doing exactly?” lol! That did make me laugh. 

Bran foretold of how the wall had been destroyed by the Night King. 

Sam met Dany, got thanked for curing Jurah of his greyscale (I just thought of him in greyscale/black and white for a second lol)  and was sad to find out she killed his dad and brother. Well, he wasn’t expecting that and was quite upset even though, as others pointed out didn’t his dad abuse him and he hated him before? So, you’d think he wouldn’t be so upset but okay.

Bran told Sam to go and tell Jon about how he’s really a Targaryen, so he went and told him in the tombs that he’s the son of  Rhaegar Targaryen and Lyanna Stark and that he’s the rightful heir to the Iron Throne. Of course … Jon was really thinking “holy cow, I slept with my auntie, what do I do now? and I’m in love with her? oh shit” - he just hopes she isn’t pregnant. 

Cersei slept with Euron, two minutes after saying if he wanted sex he should buy a whore … so, she didn’t really stick to her words at all there. She likes that he’s cocky or whatever. okay. He wants to impregnate her but she is already. 

Jaimie turned up at Winterfell in the end and saw Bran. 

Cersei also told Qyburn to get Bronn to kill her brothers with an arrow for ironic purposes. Rude. Bronn couldn’t just get laid that night lol.

Theon went and saved Yara from Euron’s ship which was cool. She like immediately punched him though lol. Theon goes to Winterfell to join the cause!

Some kid came back as a zombie for a second on some burning thing. 

Arya was super in to Gendry, more than usual. Yet he looks so much older than her and seems it. She looks 12. I feel like I dislike this ship kinda. I dunno. It’s just weird to see Arya flirt hard, she’s a crazy murdery girl lol. Then she’s all girly and it’s like out of character in a way, I dunno. They should be more brother/sister relationship like I kinda thought they had before. She also saw The Hound again!

I can’t wait to see the rest of the season! <3

I can’t believe this is the last season and I can’t wait to see how it ends! <3 

I’m also sad about it being the last season though as it’s so great ;__________;

I can’t wait to see who ends up on the Iron Throne! Will it be the rightful heir or will someone else win the game? 

Kit Harington and Nikolaj Coster-Waldau <3

title: Something Like A Gifset
body:
something like a gifset for @sherlokiness‘s unnamed chapters so i’ve decided to make something like a gifset

The Prophet - Patchface, Dance of the Dragons , flames under the sea, blue, green, and black

The Kraken’s Daughter- Sansa, wife of the Merling King. Nennymoans in her hair with silver gown.

The Soiled Knight - Undercover Jon using sex. Oathbreaker. Treasonous.

The Discarded Knight - Jon murdered by his brothers and leaves his holy order.

The Iron Captain - Undercover and drowned crow Jon coming for dragons.

The Queensguard - Sansa kneeling on Barristan’s(a true knight’s) cloak while begging for her father’s life. You just know she’s gonna have one. Rhaenyra during DotD had one. Clothed by a KG cloak twice.

The Queen’s Hand - Barristan is a “white shadow at her (Dany’s) side” while Ghost is a “white shadow at his side.” Sansa will have a Queensguard, white shadows. Or she’ll be a Targ by name.

Captain of the Guards - Jon, a Lord Commander. Leader for battle of the Dawn..Dany calls Daario her captain.

The Iron Suitor - Jon burning his hand when he steals Drogon. He has a burned hand like Vic too. Or just wielding a flaming sword, whatever that may be. Since he’s a drowned man, that makes him an Ironborn and Sansa’s suitor.

The Drowned Man - Jon, drowning in Sansa’s eyes.

The Kingbreaker -  Jon is going to break?

The Lost Lord >The Griffin Reborn- Lost Lord is a Jon? And he’ll be reborn.

“Your father.” Jaime eyed Red Ronnet’s surcoat, where two griffins faced each other on a field of red and white. Dancing griffins. “Our late Hand’s … brother, was he?”

“Cousin. Lord Jon had no brothers.”

The Reaver - Dany taking what she wants by force.

The Watcher - Jon of the NW. Jon promising to watch over Sansa after reunion. And future kids too, of course.

The Princess  in the Tower > The Queenmaker

The Princess in the Tower - Sansa, locked up in the highest tower by step-mother and step-father/secretly betrothed to a Targaryen by a father. Arianne/Dany, usurper of their brother’s throne, poisoned by a pretty boy Darkstar/Jon.

The Queenmaker - Jon, after parentage reveal.

The Wayward Bride > The King’s Prize > The Sacrifice

The Wayward Bride - betrothed four times but never to someone from the North. Snow’s maid .Runs away from her wedding and straight to Jon.

The King’s Prize - Sansa, key to the North, worth ten thousand dragons.

“The king’s prize. His Grace will be most wroth to find her gone.”

Jon is going to be really mad once Sansa goes missing.

The Sacrifice - Dany.

A Ghost in Winterfell > The Turncloak > The Prince of Winterfell

Sansa finds Jon at the wall, a Ghost. A part of them is dead. Sansa with Lady and literally Jon. Jon becomes a turncloak when he betrays Dany. He is her prince, the prince that her father promised. Or Sansa’s son will be TPTWP born in WF.

The Dragontamer > The Spurned Suitor > The Windblown > The Merchant’s Man

The Dragontamer - Jon, he’s gonna succeed where Quentyn failed. He tames and steals a dragon.Probably Drogon, he bonded with him last season.

The Spurned Suitor - Dany, after parentage reveal.  He’s gonna turn down a marriage offer from her.

The Windblown - The pack survives? Which in that case, yay!!!

The Merchant’s Man - Jon, Sansa’s last frog, is a prince. No more sloppy, minty, nor clumsy kisses. Jon will be going to Dany to barter an alliance.

Cat of the Canals - Jon seeing through Cat’s eyes, Sansa’s eyes. He’ll have one black eye (mad) and blue eye (fool.) There’s a black cat called “black bastard” which was also the “real King of the castle.” Sansa is the prize, a pearl hiding behind the name Stone.

“The biggest toms would seldom win, she noticed; oft as not, the prize went to some smaller, quicker animal, thin and mean and hungry. Like me, she told herself. Her favorite was a scrawny old tom with a chewed ear who reminded her of a cat that she’d once chased all around the Red Keep. ”

The Blind Girl - Dany when Jon chooses Sansa. She’ll be blind. By jealousy? Rage?

The Ugly Little Girl - Dany always refer to herself as a little girl. Ugly, because her heart will be corrupted. She also forgot the name of the little girl, Hazzea, because she decided to embrace her house words.

“  A little girl ran barefoot toward a big house with a red door.”

I hope this okay.

The Princess in the Tower - Sansa, locked up in the highest tower by step-mother and step-father/secretly betrothed to a Targaryen by a father. Arianne/Dany, usurper of their brother’s throne, poisoned by a pretty boy Darkstar/Jon.

The Queenmaker - Jon, after parentage reveal.

The Wayward Bride > The King’s Prize > The Sacrifice

The Wayward Bride - betrothed four times but never to someone from the North. Snow’s maid .Runs away from her wedding and straight to Jon.

The King’s Prize - Sansa, key to the North, worth ten thousand dragons.

“The king’s prize. His Grace will be most wroth to find her gone.”

Jon is going to be really mad once Sansa goes missing.

The Sacrifice - Dany.

A Ghost in Winterfell > The Turncloak > The Prince of Winterfell

Sansa finds Jon at the wall, a Ghost. A part of them is dead. Sansa with Lady and literally Jon. Jon becomes a turncloak when he betrays Dany. He is her prince, the prince that her father promised. Or Sansa’s son will be TPTWP born in WF.

The Dragontamer > The Spurned Suitor > The Windblown > The Merchant’s Man

The Dragontamer - Jon, he’s gonna succeed where Quentyn failed. He tames and steals a dragon.Probably Drogon, he bonded with him last season.

The Spurned Suitor - Dany, after parentage reveal.  He’s gonna turn down a marriage offer from her.

The Windblown - The pack survives? Which in that case, yay!!!

The Merchant’s Man - Jon, Sansa’s last frog, is a prince. No more sloppy, minty, nor clumsy kisses. Jon will be going to Dany to barter an alliance.

Cat of the Canals - Jon seeing through Cat’s eyes, Sansa’s eyes. He’ll have one black eye (mad) and blue eye (fool.) There’s a black cat called “black bastard” which was also the “real King of the castle.” Sansa is the prize, a pearl hiding behind the name Stone.

“The biggest toms would seldom win, she noticed; oft as not, the prize went to some smaller, quicker animal, thin and mean and hungry. Like me, she told herself. Her favorite was a scrawny old tom with a chewed ear who reminded her of a cat that she’d once chased all around the Red Keep. ”

The Blind Girl - Dany when Jon chooses Sansa. She’ll be blind. By jealousy? Rage?

The Ugly Little Girl - Dany always refer to herself as a little girl. Ugly, because her heart will be corrupted. She also forgot the name of the little girl, Hazzea, because she decided to embrace her house words.

“  A little girl ran barefoot toward a big house with a red door.”

I hope this okay.

summary: To be for Jaime, who yes, killed her father, but was also Kingsguard for her brother Rhaegar. And who looked up to him and held...
body:
I want this smile

To be for Jaime, who yes, killed her father, but was also Kingsguard for her brother Rhaegar. And who looked up to him and held him in high regard.

He is coming with the news that Cersei has betrayed them, but he is sticking to his word and coming to fight for them, which Daenerys will be greatful for. When the subject of his father is brought up, he will own up to what he did, but also could explain how he had a lot of love for her brother. Maybe even compare her to him as Barristan Selmy, also of that Kingsguard did.

Side note: think about Jon “just found out I’m a Targaryen”’s face in the background if someone mentions Rhaegar.

body:
Why is Bran withholding information?

Bran didn’t tell Jon and Dany that Cersei wasn’t sending troops or that she sent Euron to get the Golden Company. Why didn’t he tell Sam that his father and brother were executed for reason? And why doesn’t he tell anyone of Tyrion’s possible plot with Cersei?

He repeats himself time and time again he can tell the things that happen the past, present, and future. He could see EVERYTHING happening EVERYWHERE in the world so why doesn’t he tell ANYONE of these important things??
